<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0094-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Document: a document (not a letter) neither in the author's handwriting nor signed by the author ]">D</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0026" class="document">Orderly Book, 21 September24 November 1758.</a></p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0094-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0094-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>When Bouquet was in Raystown in early October Forbes gave him the
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-06-02-pb-0111">[111]</span>
following orders, dated and endorsed 5 Oct.: You are hereby required to order as many Gentlemen as you may imagine are competent Judges to hold a Court of Enquiry, to examine into the affair of Captain [Asher] Clayton; and to acquaint me of such Report as they shall make to you (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Alfred Procter James, ed. &lt;i&gt;Writings of General John Forbes Relating to His Service in North America&lt;/i&gt;. Menasha, Wis., 1938. ]">James, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Writings of Forbes</span></span>, 223). No report of such a court of inquiry has been found. As captain in the 2d Battalion of the Pennsylvania Regiment Clayton took part in Maj. James Grants action near Fort Duquesne on 14 September. In his lengthy account of his defeat written shortly after the event, Grant makes no mention of Captain Clayton by name; his battalion had one officer captured and five men wounded in the engagement. On 25 Sept. 1758, GW wrote George William Fairfax of the running away of the Pensylvanians.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0094-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0094-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>The seven captains, one from each corps, found 33 Barrells Good &amp; 23 to be picked (Report of Bread at Loyalhanna, 6 Nov., in Stevens, <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Donald H. Kent et al., eds. &lt;i&gt;The Papers of Henry Bouquet&lt;/i&gt;. 6 vols. Harrisburg, Pa., 1951-94. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Bouquet Papers</span></span>, 2:59697).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0094-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0094-fn-0003">3</a>
  
   <p>See the chart and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0028&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-06-02-0028-fn-0005#GEWN-02-06-02-0028-fn-0005" class="document">note 5</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0028" class="document">Orderly Book, 22 September</a>.</p>

</div>
